pbmeta:CellPac.Description: The Sequel SMRT Cell 1M (4/Pack) are nanofabricated consumables each patterned with 1,000,000 wells called zero-mode waveguides (ZMWs). They are packaged together in a streamlined 4 SMRT Cell format (4/tray). One SMRT Cell is utilized in each sequencing reaction, and experiments can be run in single or in batch mode, giving your projects a greater level of flexibility.
pbmeta:CellPac.Name: SMRT® Cell 1M v2 LR (4/Pack)

pbmeta:ControlKit.Description: The Sequel DNA Internal Control 2.0 contains a fixed template of 2 kb length bound to Sequel Binding Kit 2.0 for use as an internal sequencing control. Reagent quantities provide spike-in controls for a minimum of 24 samples.
pbmeta:ControlKit.Name: Sequel® DNA Internal Control 2.0

pbmeta:TemplatePrepKit.Description: The SMRTbell® Template Prep Kit contains reagent supplies to perform SMRTbell library preparations of primer-annealed SMRTbell libraries for insert sizes ranging from 500 bp to over 20 kb.
pbmeta:TemplatePrepKit.Name: CRISPR/Cas9 Placeholder w/ asymmetric adapters

pbmeta:BindingKit.Description: The Sequel Binding Kit 2.0 contains reagent supplies to bind prepared DNA template libraries to the Sequel Polymerase 2.0 in preparation for sequencing on the Sequel System. The result is a DNA polymerase/template complex. Sequel Binding Kit 1.0 should be used only with Sequel Sequencing Kit 2.0. Reagent quantities support 24 binding reactions.
pbmeta:BindingKit.Name: Sequel® Binding Kit 2.0

pbmeta:SequencingKitPlate.Description: The DNA Sequencing Kit contains a sequencing reagent plate with chemistry for single molecule real-time sequencing on the PacBio Sequel®. Reagent quantities support 8 sequencing reactions to be used in conjunction with SMRT® Cell 4Pac(s). (8 Cells max/Each Row supplies reagents for 1 Sequel SMRT Cell)
pbmeta:SequencingKitPlate.Name: Sequel® Dev Sequencing Plate

pbmeta:TransferResource.pbmeta:Name: PBI Collections Xfer test using Rsync+SSH
pbmeta:TransferResource.pbmeta:Description: Test Location for writing Transfer services to write to. Should be used by internal tools (PA SIM) and ICS tests
